The '''Ruusan Reformations''' were an event in the history of the [[Galactic Republic]] that limited the power of the [[Supreme Chancellor]]. The passage of the [[Emergency Powers Act]] in the lead-up to the onset of the [[Clone Wars]], as well as the [[Reflex Amendment]] to the [[Galactic Constitution]] during the conflict, made [[Darth Sidious|Sheev Palpatine]] the most powerful Chancellor since the Reformations.<ref name="Collapse of the Republic" />

The Ruusan Reformations shared a name with the [[Mid Rim Territories|Mid Rim]] [[planet]] [[Ruusan]].<ref name="SWTVE">''[[Star Wars: The Visual Encyclopedia]]''</ref><ref name="SWGA">''[[Star Wars: Galactic Atlas]]''</ref>

{{Rep-stub}}

==Behind the scenes==
The Ruusan Reformations were first mentioned in the [[canon]] sourcebook ''[[Collapse of the Republic]]''.<ref name="Collapse of the Republic" /> In the [[Star Wars Legends|''Star Wars'' Legends]] continuity, the [[Ruusan Reformations/Legends|Ruusan Reformations]] was the restructuring of the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]] after the perceived annihilation of the [[Sith/Legends|Sith]].<ref name="NEC">''[[The New Essential Chronology]]''</ref>

